    <title>
      <narrative xml:lang="en">Feasibility Study - Solar Mini-grid Deployment Feasibility Study, through Arizona State University</narrative>
    </title>
    <description type="1">
      <narrative xml:lang="en">This grant funds a feasibility study to conduct preparatory activities for the Fiji Ministry of Economy to identify mini-grid sites, conduct feasibility assessments, complete preliminary technical designs, provide geospatial mapping, compare ownership and operation models, and assess financial viability of sites in Fiji. The Study will be conducted by the Arizona State University's Laboratory for Energy and Power and deliver up to 75 priority sites that meet technical, financial, legal, ownership, and climate risk requirements.</narrative>
